:QUOTE [subtitle:Ted Chiang, quotetype:PLAIN]
The past is a foreign country: they do things differently there. But I am from there.

:JOURNEY
Reading Exhalation
Story
Enjoyment
- Exhalation | 5 | Mathematical perfection | Perfect the way a proof is perfect
- The Great Silence | 5 | Most devastating | Shortest and most emotionally gutting piece
- Anxiety Is the Dizziness | 5 | Most original | Best use of multiverse I have read
- Omphalos | 4 | Quietly brave | Conclusion I continue to think about

:NOTE
Reading Ted Chiang slowly is the correct pace. One story a week lets each idea \
settle before the next one arrives. Rushing through this collection is a waste of it.

